<p>One in 10 Canadians cannot afford prescription meds</p>
<p>CTV News: Canada lacks universal drug coverage</p>
<p>Although Canada has publicly funded health care for hospital and physician services, the country lacks universal drug coverage. Avis Favaro reports.</p>
<p>Canada AM: Dr. Marla Shapiro on pricey prescriptions</p>
<p>Canada AM's medical specialist explains how a new study shows one in ten Canadians are having problems affording medications they have been prescribed, while one in four people without drug insurance cannot afford to have their prescriptions filled at all.</p>
